======================================================================
PART 7: CHEBYSHEV POLYNOMIALS — THE BRIDGE
======================================================================

  Chebyshev at x = phi/2 = 0.809017:
  T_n(phi/2): [1, 0.809, 0.309, -0.309, -0.809, -1.0, -0.809, -0.309, 0.309, 0.809, 1.0, 0.809]
  Compare F_n/2^(n-1): [0, 1.0, 0.5, 0.5, 0.375, 0.3125, 0.25, 0.203125, 0.1640625, 0.1328125, 0.107421875, 0.0869140625]

  The 2-3 recurrence F(n) = 2*F(n-2) + F(n-3):
  This is a DEPTH-3 Chebyshev variant!
  Characteristic polynomial: x^3 = 2x + 1
  = x^3 - 2x - 1 = (x+1)(x^2-x-1) = (x+1)*Phi_Fib(x)

  Roots of x^3 - 2x - 1 = 0:
    x = 1.618034 = phi!
    x = -1.000000 = -1!
    x = -0.618034 = -1/phi!

  (x+1)(x^2-x-1) expanded:
  = x^3 - x^2 - x + x^2 - x - 1 = x^3 - 2x - 1  CHECK!

  THE 2-3 FIBONACCI RECURRENCE FACTORS AS:
  (period-2 part) * (golden ratio part)
  The -1 root gives period 2: (-1)^n alternates
  The phi root gives growth: phi^n
  Together: F(n) = A*phi^n + B*(-1/phi)^n + C*(-1)^n
  But we know F(n) = (phi^n - (-1/phi)^n)/sqrt(5)
  The extra (-1)^n part is the residue from the 2-3 decomposition

