PART 8: EISENSTEIN + FIBONACCI = ICOSAHEDRAL SYMMETRY?
======================================================================

  PSL(2,4) = PSL(2,5) = A_5: the EXCEPTIONAL ISOMORPHISM
  |PSL(2,4)| = (4^2-1)*(4^2-4)/2 = 15*12/2 = 60? No...
  |PSL(2,q)| = q(q^2-1)/gcd(2,q-1)
  |PSL(2,4)| = 4*(16-1)/1 = 60
  |PSL(2,5)| = 5*(25-1)/2 = 60
  |A_5| = 60
  ALL EQUAL 60 = 3*4*5 = n(n-1)(n-2) at n=5!
  And 60 is the denominator of the n=5 deviation: Var/Mean^2 = 19/60!!

  THE A_5 CONNECTION:
  - A_5 is the rotation symmetry of the ICOSAHEDRON
  - The icosahedron has 12 vertices, 30 edges, 20 faces
  - 20 faces = C(6,3) (triangulations of the hexagon)
  - 30 edges = C(6,2)*2 (pairs of consecutive elements)
  - 12 vertices = 2*6 (antipodal pairs)

  Icosahedron: V=12, E=30, F=20
  Euler: V - E + F = 12 - 30 + 20 = 2  CHECK
  Each vertex has degree 5
  Dual = dodecahedron: V=20, E=30, F=12

  60 = |A_5| = |PSL(2,4)| = |PSL(2,5)|
  60 = n(n-1)(n-2) at n=5
  60 = denominator of Var/Mean^2 = 19/60 at n=5
  Var/Mean^2 = 19/60 = 1/3 - 1/60
  So: deviation = 1/|A_5| = 1/|PSL(2,4)| = 1/|PSL(2,5)|!
  THE DEVIATION FROM THE CONE IS 1/|A_5|!

