  1/Phi_3(1) = 1/3 = 20/60
  1/Phi_3(1) - 1/A_5 = 1/3 - 1/60 = 19/60
  So: Var/Mean^2 = 1/Phi_3(1) - 1/|PSL(2, Phi_3(1)+1)|
  Because: PSL(2,4) = PSL(2, Phi_3(1)+1) = A_5, |A_5|=60

  19 = 2^5 - 13 = 32 - |PG(2,3)|
  19 = Phi_3(1) * Phi_3(2) - 2 = 3*7 - 2 = 21 - 2 = 19
  Wait: 3*7 = 21, not 19. Let me reconsider.
  19 = 20 - 1 = 4*5 - 1 = (Phi_3(1)+1)*(Phi_3(1)+2) - 1
  19 is a UNIQUE prime: it's the number of rotational symmetries
  of the regular 19-gon that are not trivial

