PART 12: THE PERIOD-6 FIBONACCI CONE
======================================================================

  Fibonacci mod 4 (period 6):
    F( 0) mod 4 = 0  (angle =   0 deg)
    F( 1) mod 4 = 1  (angle =  60 deg)
    F( 2) mod 4 = 1  (angle = 120 deg)
    F( 3) mod 4 = 2  (angle = 180 deg)
    F( 4) mod 4 = 3  (angle = 240 deg)
    F( 5) mod 4 = 1  (angle = 300 deg)
    F( 6) mod 4 = 0  (angle =   0 deg)
    F( 7) mod 4 = 1  (angle =  60 deg)
    F( 8) mod 4 = 1  (angle = 120 deg)
    F( 9) mod 4 = 2  (angle = 180 deg)
    F(10) mod 4 = 3  (angle = 240 deg)
    F(11) mod 4 = 1  (angle = 300 deg)
    F(12) mod 4 = 0  (angle =   0 deg)

  The 6 states form a HEXAGONAL cycle in mod-4 space:
  State: (F_n mod 4, F_{n+1} mod 4)
    Step 0: (0, 1)
    Step 1: (1, 1)
    Step 2: (1, 2)
    Step 3: (2, 3)
    Step 4: (3, 1)
    Step 5: (1, 0)
  Return to start: (0, 1) = (0, 1)
  Same as step 0? True

  THE HEXAGONAL-CONIC CONNECTION:
  A regular hexagon = cube section perpendicular to (1,1,1)
  The (1,1,1) direction = the 'cone axis' in 3D
  Period 6 = one full rotation around the cone axis
  The 6 Fibonacci states = 6 vertices of the hexagonal cross-section
  The cone dimension 3 × rotation period 2 = 6 = Fibonacci period mod 4

